io.spine.server

Class BoundedContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.integration.grpc.IntegrationEventSubscriberGrpc.IntegrationEventSubscriberImplBase
      • io.spine.server.BoundedContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.grpc.BindableService, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public abstract class BoundedContext
extends io.spine.server.integration.grpc.IntegrationEventSubscriberGrpc.IntegrationEventSubscriberImplBase
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
    A logical and structural boundary of a model.

    Logically, a bounded context represents a sub-system, built to be described with the same ubiquitous language. Any term within a single bounded context has a single meaning and may or may not map to another term in the language of another bounded context.

    The ubiquitous language of a bounded context is represented by the entity state, event, and command types, entity types, etc. An entity and its adjacent types belong to the bounded context, which the entity Repository is registered in.

    Structurally, a bounded context brings together all the infrastructure required for the components of a model to cooperate.

    An instance of BoundedContext acts as a major point of configuration for all the model elements which belong to it.

    See Also:
    Blog post on bounded contexts

      • register

        public <I,E extends Entity<I,?>> void register(Repository<I,E> repository)
        Registers the passed repository with the BoundedContext.

        If the repository does not have a storage assigned, it will be initialized using the StorageFactory associated with this bounded context.

        Checks whether there is a default state for entity type.

        Type Parameters:
        I - the type of IDs used in the repository
        E - the type of entities or aggregates
        Parameters:
        repository - the repository to register
        See Also:

      • close

        public void close()
           throws java.lang.Exception
        Closes the BoundedContext performing all necessary clean-ups.

        This method performs the following:

        1. Closes associated StorageFactory.
        2. Closes CommandBus.
        3. Closes EventBus.
        4. Closes IntegrationBus.
        5. Closes CommandStore.
        6. Closes EventStore.
        7. Closes Stand.
        8. Shuts down all registered repositories. Each registered repository is:
          • un-registered from CommandBus
          • un-registered from EventBus
          • detached from its storage
        Specified by:
        close in interface java.lang.AutoCloseable
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - caused by closing one of the components
